Subject: Issues with Filesystem FSAA Bulk Import
Description:
Hello,

Bulk import for Filesystem FSAA is failing with the following Error messages

Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.FSAAException: Tier 2 database does not match Tier 1 data; Access data needs to be reset in order to import this data. To reset scan data, set AccessGUID to 'RESET' in the SA_FSAA_Hosts table (all existing Access data in Tier 1 will be deleted!) at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.Util.RunInBackground[TResult](Action statusAction, Func`1 execAction) at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.Util.RunInBackground(Action statusAction, Action execAction) at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.BulkImportTask.InternalProcessRecord() at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.Tasks.Task.StartExecute()


User does not have permission to perform this action.
Solution_Comment__c:
[Issue]
Customer is receiving errors on the FSAA Bulk Import: "Tier 2 database does not match Tier 1 data; Access data needs to be reset in order to import this data. To reset scan data, set AccessGUID to 'RESET' in the SA_FSAA_Hosts table

[Resolution]
Used the Maintenance > Reset hosts option in the FSAA Query to repair the GUIDs
